PERFORMANCE
BUDGETINGSYSTEM /Ministry of Finance, Planning & 
Economic Development, UgandaCASE STUDY

Ministry of Finance Planning and Economic Department, Uganda 
(MoFPED) expanded its service delivery by increasing and implementing an Output Budgeting Tool (OBT) in 2009-10 to facilitate the groundwork of budget preparation documents by government ministries, agencies and local governments (MALGs) and their consolidation by MoFPED. The system was useful in linking financial budgets with results (outputs) of MALGs.
The Government of Uganda (GoU) implemented the decentralization 
policy as one of the major policy reforms to ensure good governance and improved service delivery. As a means of improving Budget management and administration in MoFPED, GoU implemented an Output Budgeting System. This is a computerized budgeting tool, planning, preparation and reporting system which aims at enabling Governments plan and use their financial resources more effectively and efficiently.
The modules covered in the implementation included:- Budget 
Planning, Ministerial Policy Statement, Budget Estimates, Execution and Reporting.
The business objectives included:-
The Web based budgeting tool provided a solution for budgeting process which not only depended on just a single document—it was a year-long cycle whose different phases offered civil society varying access points to influence how public resources were raised and spent and ultimately influenced the budget’s desired outcomes.
This “budget cycle” was broken down into four major events or 
stages, namely:• Formulation—when the executive branch puts together the budget plan
• Approval—when the legislature debates, alters (if it has the power to do so), and approves the budget plan
• Execution (implementation, monitoring, and control)—when the government implements the policies in the budget
• Oversight (auditing and legislative assessment)—when the national audit institution and the legislature account for and assess the expenditures made under the budgetClient:
Economic Department, Uganda (MoFPED) 
Industry:
Public Sector
Business Situation:
GoU was looking to implement Performance budgeting system to facilitate the budget preparation by government ministries, agencies and local governments.
Solution:
Techno Brain implemented its Performance Budgeting System built on MS SharePoint 2013 and SQL which included budget planning, preparation, and execution, reporting and interfacing with public finance IFMS, IPPS and Donor Aid Management System
Benefits:
• Real time access to information; 
• Increased efficiency through an integrated solution;
• Quick and effective decision-making.
