Scope of workTechno Brain implemented a Performance Budgeting System 
built on MS SharePoint 2013 and SQL. Techno Brain delivered a comprehensive solution which included budget planning, preparation, execution, reporting and Interfacing with Public Finance IFMS, IPPS and Donor Aid Management System, providing an end to end solution for addressing all the issues arising from a decentralized system.
The solution helped the MoFPED Uganda to streamline their 
budgeting process and improve their performance based on the information available from MDA’s, sectors and local governments. The solution also enhanced management’s visibility on the activities being executed at the government level and automated the whole budgeting process, thus eliminating the overhead of compiling the information received from various sources and reentering the financial information in the system at the MoFPED.
Performance-based budgeting system also referred as outcome 
budgeting for developing budgets based on the relationship between funding and expected results. Improved cost-efficiency and manages effective budgeting outlays, increasing visibility into how government policies translate into spending and making systematic use of performance information. 
System understands the key components of Budgeting: Inputs, Outputs and expected Outcomes.  System links up 
performance information chain, inputs (resources) link to outcomes (macro goals) via change from the goods or services of those outputs.
The benefits of PBS are multi-fold:• Compliance 
